      • createSubreactionData

        public org.sbml.jsbml.xml.XMLNode createSubreactionData(java.lang.String id,
                                                        double keff,
                                                        java.util.List<java.lang.String> enzymeReferences,
                                                        java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> elementContributions,
                                                        java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesReferences,
                                                        java.util.List<java.lang.Double> stoichiometries)
        Create an XMLNode of the new SubreactionData object for the list of SubreactionData.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the subreaction
        keff - the effective turnover rate of the enzymes in the subreaction
        enzymeReferences - list with ids of enzymes that catalyze the subreaction, may be null
        elementContributions - map containing net element contributions to a macromolecule, may be null
        speciesReferences - list with the ids of all species in the reaction
        stoichiometries - list with all species stoichiometries in the reaction, must have the same order as the list with species ids
        Returns:
        the XMLNode containing the SubreactionData

      • createTranslocationData

        public org.sbml.jsbml.xml.XMLNode createTranslocationData(java.lang.String id,
                                                          double keff,
                                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> enzymeReferences,
                                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Boolean> fixedKeff,
                                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Boolean> listLengthDependent,
                                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesReferences,
                                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Double> stoichiometries,
                                                          boolean lengthDependentEnergy)
        Create an XMLNode of the new SubreactionData object for the list of TranslocationData.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the subreaction
        keff - the effective turnover rate of the enzymes in the translocation
        enzymeReferences - list with ids of enzymes that catalyze the subreaction, may be null
        fixedKeff - list with information whether an enzyme coupling has a fixed keff in the translocation process
        listLengthDependent - list with information whether the enzyme coupling is length dependent in the translocation process
        speciesReferences - list with ids of species used in the translocation process
        stoichiometries - list with stoichiometries of species in the translocation process
        lengthDependentEnergy - whether the ATP cost of the translocation is dependent on the length of the protein
        Returns:
        the XMLNode containing the TranslocationData
